119
00:04:32,559 --> 00:04:35,559
with a top border and a right border, like this.

120
00:04:35,559 --> 00:04:38,359
And then, I rotate it to simulate the tip of an arrow.

121
00:04:38,359 --> 00:04:39,359
So there you go, we rotate the thing.

122
00:04:39,359 --> 00:04:42,359
And the thing is that afterwards, on hover, basically,

123
00:04:42,359 --> 00:04:44,359
so if we display the hover, it's on the button

124
00:04:44,359 --> 00:04:45,359
that I'm going to put the hover.

125
00:04:47,359 --> 00:04:49,359
We see that our arrow is still rotated,

126
00:04:49,359 --> 00:04:51,359
to keep the arrow look, you know.

127
00:04:51,359 --> 00:04:54,359
And then, we translate it like that to the right.

128
00:04:54,359 --> 00:04:57,359
For me, to solve that, actually, in the test,

129
00:04:57,359 --> 00:04:59,359
I removed the translate here.

130
00:04:59,359 --> 00:05:03,359
There, basically, and I applied it on top.

131
00:05:03,359 --> 00:05:04,359
I applied it here, basically.

132
00:05:04,359 --> 00:05:07,359
Transform, Translate, 30 pixels.

133
00:05:08,359 --> 00:05:10,359
And I also removed it from the body.

134
00:05:11,359 --> 00:05:12,359
I had solved the thing like that.

135
00:05:12,359 --> 00:05:14,359
Rather than applying the translate on,

136
00:05:14,359 --> 00:05:17,359
and the tip of the arrow, and the body of the arrow,

137
00:05:17,359 --> 00:05:20,359
I had applied it on the parent.

138
00:05:20,359 --> 00:05:21,359
I had applied it on the whole thing,

139
00:05:21,359 --> 00:05:22,359
which moved like that, actually.

140
00:05:22,359 --> 00:05:26,359
But I could have kept my solution as I created it

141
00:05:26,359 --> 00:05:28,359
