147
00:05:44,359 --> 00:05:45,359
What is this craziness?

148
00:05:45,359 --> 00:05:47,359
I had no idea about that at all,

149
00:05:47,359 --> 00:05:48,359
but actually, what we learn here,

150
00:05:48,359 --> 00:05:50,359
what we watch together,

151
00:05:50,359 --> 00:05:53,359
is that the order in transforms is important.

152
00:05:53,359 --> 00:05:54,359
If you first do a rotate,

153
00:05:54,359 --> 00:05:57,359
and then translate along the X-axis,

154
00:05:57,359 --> 00:05:59,359
the X-axis will be like that down.

155
00:05:59,359 --> 00:06:01,359
On the other hand, if you first do a translate,

156
00:06:01,359 --> 00:06:03,359
and then do a rotate,

157
00:06:03,359 --> 00:06:04,359
it will happen like this.

158
00:06:04,359 --> 00:06:05,359
This thing is completely mind-blowing

159
00:06:05,359 --> 00:06:07,359
that the order in translate was important.

160
00:06:07,359 --> 00:06:08,359
I didn't know that,

161
00:06:08,359 --> 00:06:10,359
and I think very few front-end developers

162
00:06:10,359 --> 00:06:11,359
know that, actually.

163
00:06:11,359 --> 00:06:12,359
